OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773907468
OL,3,CKing Charles holds adapted state
OL,4,Cbanquet for Nigerian president
OL,6,FA royal aide said: "The visiting
OL,7,Fpresident is observing Ramadan and is
OL,8,Fa Muslim, so we have made some
OL,9,Fadjustments to what's been happening
OL,10,Ftoday.
OL,12,F"At the moment, guests that are
OL,13,Fstaying in the castle are observing
OL,14,Fiftar, so breaking fast, but we do
OL,15,Frecognise that for some of the guests
OL,16,Fthat are attending this evening, iftar
OL,17,Fwill take place when they're
OL,18,Ftravelling in the car so we've
OL,19,Fprovided a space in the castle where
OL,20,Fthey can pray on arrival.
OL,26,@nD@TOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773907468
OL,3,CKing Charles holds adapted state
OL,4,Cbanquet for Nigerian president
OL,6,F"And we are going to serve canapes for
OL,7,Fthe first time, pre-banquet reception,
OL,8,Fand that will provide sustenance
OL,9,Fbecause after speeches, people don't
OL,10,Factually start having the banquet
OL,11,Funtil 9 o'clock."
OL,13,FA special mocktail has also been
OL,14,Fdesigned to celebrate the state visit.
OL,15,FThe King introduced the tradition of
OL,16,Fserving a bespoke after-banquet
OL,17,Fcocktail, but usually the drink is
OL,18,Falcoholic.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
