OL,3,CKing Charles holds adapted state
OL,4,Cbanquet for Nigerian president
OL,6,FEngland rugby captain Maro Itoje and
OL,7,Fhis wife Mimi, Olympic 400m gold
OL,8,Fmedallist Christine Ohuruogu, former
OL,9,FLioness and football pundit Eni Aluko,
OL,10,Fspace scientist Dame Maggie Aderin,
OL,11,Fbroadcaster Ade Adepitan, singer Tiwa
OL,12,FSavage and the UK's first black female
OL,13,FMichelin-starred chef Adejoke Bakare
OL,14,Fare among the 160 guests who have
OL,15,Fgathered with the King, the Queen and
OL,16,Fthe Prince and Princess of Wales.
OL,18,FGuests are dining on a menu of:
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/7
